@startuml
!theme plain
title CollegeLMS — Deployment Diagram

node "VPS (Cloud.ru)" {
  rectangle "Docker Host" {

    database "PostgreSQL 16" as DB {
      [collegelms]
    }

    database "Redis 7" as Redis {
      [sessions]
      [rate_limits]
      [token_blacklist]
    }

    component "nginx\n(loadbalancer)" as Nginx {
      port "80"
      port "443"
    }

    component "ASP.NET Core 10\nCollegeLMS.API" as API {
      port "8080"
      [Rest API]
      [Swagger UI]
      [Health Checks]
    }

    component "Next.js 14\nCollegeLMS.Next" as Frontend {
      port "3000"
      [Static Pages]
      [App Router]
      [shadcn/ui]
    }

    component ".NET 10\nCollegeLMS.TelegramBot" as Bot {
      port "5030"
      [Schedule Bot]
      [Max Bot]
      [OpenCode Integration]
    }

    folder "uploads" as Uploads {
      [Materials]
      [Submissions]
    }

    folder "import" as Import {
      [wp_data_full.json]
    }
  }
}

rectangle "GitHub" {
  [GitHub Actions] as GHA
  [Source Code] as Repo
}

rectangle "stvcc.ru\n(WordPress)" as WP {
  [REST API]
}

rectangle "Telegram" {
  [Telegram API] as TG
}

rectangle "OpenCode Server" as OC {
  [SSE / HTTP API]
}

GHA --> Nginx: git push → SSH deploy
Repo --> GHA: push trigger
WP --> API: WordPress import (UC-6)
API --> DB: Entity Framework
API --> Redis: Session + rate limiting
API --> Uploads: File storage
API --> Import: WP data
Frontend --> API: REST API + JWT
Nginx --> Frontend: / → Next.js
Nginx --> API: /api/ → .NET
Nginx --> API: /swagger → Swagger
Bot --> TG: Telegram API
Bot --> API: Schedule data
Bot --> OC: OpenCode integration
@enduml
